[ctns_make id='gen_abs_prop_x_equals_y']

  [ctns_front style='font-size:150%;']
$$ |x| = |y| $$
  [/ctns_front]  

  [ctns_back style='font-size:100%;']
$| |x| = |y| |$ is equivalent to $| x = \pm y |$
  [/ctns_back]  

  [ctns_frontspeak]
The absolute value of x equals the absolute value of y.
  [/ctns_frontspeak]  

  [ctns_backspeak]
When the absolute value of x equals the absolute value of why, then x equals plus or minus why.
  [/ctns_backspeak]  

[/ctns_make]
